In this article, President Joe Biden addresses world leaders at the virtual Leaders Summit on Climate. He expresses gratitude for the leaders who have committed to helping combat climate change and emphasizes the need for collective action. Biden highlights the opportunity that addressing climate change presents, such as creating millions of good-paying jobs in innovative sectors. He discusses the importance of investing in clean energy technologies and infrastructure to create a sustainable future. The President announces that the United States will be joining efforts to decarbonize critical sectors, including industry, power, and agriculture, and expresses willingness to collaborate with other countries, including Russia, on carbon dioxide removal. Biden also emphasizes the economic benefits of transitioning to a cleaner economy and announces the launch of a Global Partnership for Climate-Smart Infrastructure. He concludes by thanking world leaders for their commitment and reiterates his belief in working together to confront the climate crisis and build a better future.